## M19(2/6): raw `%x` access inside an `unsafe` block is allowed.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 35 (M19 design): the `unsafe` block is the
## statement-level audit boundary. Any operation that requires
## unsafe context (raw `%x`, unsafe builtins, unsafe-fn calls,
## extern calls) is allowed inside; nothing else changes about
## the surrounding scope. Parallel to Rust's `unsafe { ... }`
## block ergonomics.

sub main()
  x = 7
  unsafe
    r = %x         # `(raw x)` — raw access, requires unsafe
    print(r)
